209. He says (in NERONE cap. 30.) that a portico or piazza of it was 3000 feet long; "tanta laxitas ut porticus triplices milliarias haberet." He cannot mean three miles. For the whole extent of the house from the PALATINE to the ESQUILINE was not near so great. So when VOPISC. in AURELIANO mentions a portico in [p:*Sallust*]'s gardens, which he calls _porticus milliarensis_, it must be understood of a thousand feet. So also [p:*Horace*];

> - $Nulla decempedis$
> - $Metata privatis opacam$
> - $Porticus excipiebat Arcton.$ [Lib. 2. ode 15.]

So also in lib. 1. satyr. 8.

> - $Mille pedes in fronte, trecentos cippus in agrum$
> - $Hic dabat.$

