252. "Nec numero Hispanos, nec robore Gallos, nec calliditate Poenos, nec artibus Graecos, nec denique hoc ipso hujus gentis, ac terrae domestico nativoque sensu, Italos ipsos ac Latinos --superavimus." _De harusp. resp_. cap. 9. The disorders of [l:*Spain*] seem to have been almost proverbial: "Nec impacatos a tergo horrebis Iberos." _Virg. Georg_. lib. 3. The IBERI are here plainly taken, by a poetical figure, for robbers in general.

